verses.text_plain: Make a joyful noise unto God, all ye lands:
verses.verse_html:
1Make a joyful noise unto God, all ye lands: ▼
▼ all…: Heb. all the earth

footnotes.body_html: ▼ all…: Heb. all the earth

verses.text_plain: Sing forth the honour of his name: make his praise glorious.
verses.verse_html: 2Sing forth the honour of his name: make his praise glorious.

verses.text_plain: Say unto God, How terrible art thou in thy works! through the greatness of thy power shall thine enemies submit themselves unto thee.
verses.verse_html:
3Say unto God, How terrible art thou in thy works! through the greatness of thy power shall thine enemies submit themselves unto thee. ▼
▼ submit…: or, yield feigned obedience: Heb. lie

footnotes.body_text: ▼ submit…: or, yield feigned obedience: Heb. lie
footnotes.body_html: ▼ submit…: or, yield feigned obedience: Heb. lie

verses.text_plain: All the earth shall worship thee, and shall sing unto thee; they shall sing to thy name. Selah.
verses.verse_html: 4All the earth shall worship thee, and shall sing unto thee; they shall sing to thy name. Selah.

verses.text_plain: Come and see the works of God: he is terrible in his doing toward the children of men.
verses.verse_html: 5Come and see the works of God: he is terrible in his doing toward the children of men.

verses.text_plain: He turned the sea into dry land: they went through the flood on foot: there did we rejoice in him.
verses.verse_html: 6He turned the sea into dry land: they went through the flood on foot: there did we rejoice in him.

verses.text_plain: He ruleth by his power for ever; his eyes behold the nations: let not the rebellious exalt themselves. Selah.
verses.verse_html: 7He ruleth by his power for ever; his eyes behold the nations: let not the rebellious exalt themselves. Selah.

verses.text_plain: O bless our God, ye people, and make the voice of his praise to be heard:
verses.verse_html: 8O bless our God, ye people, and make the voice of his praise to be heard:

verses.text_plain: Which holdeth our soul in life, and suffereth not our feet to be moved.
verses.verse_html:
9Which holdeth our soul in life, and suffereth not our feet to be moved. ▼
▼ holdeth: Heb. putteth

verses.text_plain: For thou, O God, hast proved us: thou hast tried us, as silver is tried.
verses.verse_html: 10For thou, O God, hast proved us: thou hast tried us, as silver is tried.

verses.text_plain: Thou broughtest us into the net; thou laidst affliction upon our loins.
verses.verse_html: 11Thou broughtest us into the net; thou laidst affliction upon our loins.

verses.text_plain: Thou hast caused men to ride over our heads; we went through fire and through water: but thou broughtest us out into a wealthy place.
verses.verse_html:
12Thou hast caused men to ride over our heads; we went through fire and through water: but thou broughtest us out into a wealthy place. ▼
▼ wealthy: Heb. moist

verses.text_plain: I will go into thy house with burnt offerings: I will pay thee my vows,
verses.verse_html: 13I will go into thy house with burnt offerings: I will pay thee my vows,

verses.text_plain: Which my lips have uttered, and my mouth hath spoken, when I was in trouble.
verses.verse_html:
14Which my lips have uttered, and my mouth hath spoken, when I was in trouble. ▼
▼ uttered: Heb. opened

verses.text_plain: I will offer unto thee burnt sacrifices of fatlings, with the incense of rams; I will offer bullocks with goats. Selah.
verses.verse_html:
15I will offer unto thee burnt sacrifices of fatlings, with the incense of rams; I will offer bullocks with goats. Selah. ▼
▼ fatlings: Heb. marrow

verses.text_plain: Come and hear, all ye that fear God, and I will declare what he hath done for my soul.
verses.verse_html: 16Come and hear, all ye that fear God, and I will declare what he hath done for my soul.

verses.text_plain: I cried unto him with my mouth, and he was extolled with my tongue.
verses.verse_html: 17I cried unto him with my mouth, and he was extolled with my tongue.

verses.text_plain: If I regard iniquity in my heart, the Lord will not hear me:
verses.verse_html: 18If I regard iniquity in my heart, the Lord will not hear me:

verses.text_plain: But verily God hath heard me; he hath attended to the voice of my prayer.
verses.verse_html: 19But verily God hath heard me; he hath attended to the voice of my prayer.

verses.text_plain: Blessed be God, which hath not turned away my prayer, nor his mercy from me.
verses.verse_html: 20Blessed be God, which hath not turned away my prayer, nor his mercy from me.
